# Recruitment project ‚Üî candidates

## Relation row

- Table: `u_yf_projekty_rekrutacyjne_relations_members_entity` (`crmid` = project, `relcrmid` = candidate).
- Handler: `GetRelatedMembers` ‚Äî use **`createMembership($projectId, $candidateId, $status)`** for inserts.
- Do **not** change `create(int, int): bool` signature on the parent `GetRelatedList` (PHP fatal). Parent `create()` must stay 2-arg; throw or delegate if called without status.

## Initial status contract

| Source | `recruitment_status_rel` |
|--------|--------------------------|
| CV / `CandidateApplicationSideEffects::bindCandidateToProject` | `PPL_APPLIED` via `createLink(..., STATUS_APPLIED)` |
| Manual (kanban +, related-list Select, `RelationAjax`) | `PPL_MANUALLY_ADDED` via `save_related_module` ‚Üí `createMembership` |

`cvs_applied_number` counts only `PPL_APPLIED`. New status must be added to `RelationTrigger::getRecruitmentStatusOptions()` and `RecruitmentStatusTransition::SUGGESTED_DEFAULTS`.

## Kanban widget (summary tab)

- Load project via `ProjektyRekrutacyjne\Models\Record::getInstanceById()` ‚Äî `getRelatedCandidates()` is module-specific (not on `Base\Models\Record`); add `/** @var \App\Modules\ProjektyRekrutacyjne\Models\Record $project */` for Intelephense. Same pattern as `CandidatesRecruitmentProjects` widget.
- Rendered server-side in `SummaryViewWidgets.tpl` (`RecruitmentProjectKanban.tpl`) ‚Äî **not** a `widgetContainer_*` AJAX widget.
- **Layout (4 tables):** (1) `PPL_MANUALLY_ADDED` alone ‚Äî ‚ÄûDobre kandydatury‚Äù + (+); (2) screening ‚Äî 3 cols @ 33% (`.recruitment-kanban-screening`); (3‚Äì4) interview + rejections ‚Äî 4 cols @ 25% each (`.recruitment-kanban-quarters`). Wrapper: `.recruitment-project-kanban`.
- **Styles:** `public/modules/ProjektyRekrutacyjne/resources/RecruitmentProjectKanban.css` ‚Äî loaded in `Views/Detail.php` ‚Üí `getHeaderCss()`; minify after edit. No inline `<style>` in tpl.
- **`loadWidgets()` does not refresh the kanban.** After manual add, update chips in the DOM (`Detail.js` ‚Üí `refreshUiAfterManualCandidatesAdd`) or return candidate payloads from `AddManualCandidatesAjax`.
- (+) button: `AddManualCandidatesAjax` + `Vtiger_Popup_Js` multi-select `Candidates`.

## Manual-add UX (do not regress)

- No success toast on add (chips appearing is enough).
- All candidates already linked: info skip message only ‚Äî **not** `PLL_NO_SUCH_RECORD`. API: `success` true when `added` or `skipped` non-empty; JS must not treat skip-only as failure.

## Side effects

- `relateEntities(..., 'getRelatedMembers')` ‚Üí `EntityAfterLink` ‚Üí `NewCandidateInProject` (comments differ for applied vs manual).
- Import uses `createLink()` directly (not `relateEntities`) to keep `PPL_APPLIED` and still run the same handler.

## Candidates module rename (metadata gotchas)

- **RecruitmentApplication related tab** on Candidates Detail: needs `vtiger_fieldmodulerel.relmodule = 'Candidates'` on `candidate_id` (field 303290). Stale `Kandydaci` ‚Üí HTTP 500 in `RelationListView::getCreateViewUrl()`.
- **Picklist fields** (`status`, `availability`, `work_time_type`): table must match field name (`vtiger_candidate_status`, etc.) ‚Äî see `m260609_000006`.
- **Verification**: `bin/check_candidates_migration.php` after migrations; migrations `m260609_000001`‚Äì`000007` in `migrations/Users/`.

## Kanban status change + transition mail

- Manual drag: `Detail.js` ‚Üí `ChangeCandidateStatusManuallyAjax` ‚Üí `GetRelatedMembers::changeStatus()` (whitelist: `RecruitmentStatusTransition`).
- Transition mail matrix: `RecruitmentStatusTransitionMail::resolveMailActions()` splits by `delivery_mode` ‚Äî **`auto`** ‚Üí `sendAutoTemplates()` + JSON `autoSend` toast; **`prompt`** ‚Üí JSON `mailPrompt.templateIds` ‚Üí `Vtiger_Index_Js.triggerSendEmailModal` (`Candidates`, `sourceModule`/`sourceRecord` = project). See `recruitment-settings.mdc`.
- Screening Accept/Reject and workflows do **not** use the mail matrix.

## Candidate files (CV, consents, etc.)

- **Canonical storage:** Documents module + `vtiger_senotesrel` ‚Äî Candidate detail ‚Üí Wiƒôcej ‚Üí **Documents** (`getAttachments`, `m260613_000006`). ADD/SELECT + per-row **CV** (Set as CV) via `RelatedListLeftSideExtras`.
- **Preview only:** Summary widget **`CandidatesPreview`** (`CandidatesPreview.tpl`) reads **`cv_img_file`** (uitype **330**, JSON array in `u_yf_candidates`). **No widget title in template** ‚Äî image only (`.summaryWidgetContainer--cv-preview`). Empty if no Set-as-CV / transform yet, even when Documents exist. First summary column (`m260616_000002`; DB widget label is config-only). Header thumbnail: `DetailViewHeaderTitle.tpl` via `Record::getCVPathname()`.
- **Image URL:** `/file.php?module=Candidates&action=MultiAttachment&field=cv_img_file&record={id}&key={key}` ‚Äî handler `Candidates/Files/MultiAttachment.php`. Requires login (session cookie); unauthenticated ‚Üí 401 blank `<img>`.
- **UiType 330:** `MultiAttachmentJson` ‚Äî `getDBValue()` JSON-encodes arrays; `isAjaxEditable()` false (SaveAjax inline edit once wrote literal `"Array"` into DB).
- **Template pitfalls:** never `height="100%"` on preview `<img>` without a fixed-height parent (Firefox collapses to 0px). Do not Smarty `escape:'url'` on `file.php` URLs (over-encodes). Use explicit `max-width:100%; height:auto` (`.candidates-cv-preview__image`).
- **CV import:** `DocumentHelper::saveAndDeleteFile` links new Document to **Candidates** only (`prepareRelationsString('Candidates', ‚Ä¶)`).
- **Counts:** `u_yf_candidatescf.documents_count` via `RefreshDocsNumber` on link/unlink.
- **Export CV ZIP** (`Candidates/Actions/ExportCvZip.php`, mass action on related list) must follow **`cv_img_file`** (the one Set-as-CV doc), **not** filter Documents by `title='cv'` ‚Äî titles are free-form (`CV2015`, ‚Ä¶) and Set-as-CV does not rename the Document. Resolve source doc via `Record::getCurrentCvSourceDocumentId()` (`sourceDocumentId` in the JSON, written by `transformDocumentToCV()`; legacy fallback parses `{notesid}_{hash}` from `name`); if the source Document is gone, fall back to the stored `cv_img_file` blob (`resolveCvImgFileAbsolutePath()` ‚Üí `MultiAttachment::resolveAbsolutePath()`, now `public static`). One file per candidate.

## Related-list Excel export (Eksport do Excel)

- Project‚ÜíCandidates related list uses **`QuickExport::ExportRelatedToExcel`** (not the cvid-based `ExportToExcel`). Triggered by `ProjektyRekrutacyjne_RelatedList_Js.triggerQuickExportToExcel()` (`public/modules/ProjektyRekrutacyjne/resources/RelatedList.js`), which posts `parentModule`, `record`, `relatedModule`, `tab_label`, `mode=ExportRelatedToExcel`, `selected_ids`.
- Server rebuilds the **same `RelationListView`** as the view: columns from `getHeaders()` (incl. `recruitment_status_rel`), rows via new `RelationListView::getEntriesByIds($ids)` (filters `id` on the relation query, keeps Screening tab condition). Cell render mirrors `RelatedListContents.tpl` 3-rule logic ‚Äî name/uitype-4 ‚Üí `getDisplayValue`, `fromOutsideList` ‚Üí `Field::getDisplayValue` (translated picklist label for status), else `getListViewDisplayValue`.
- The old cvid path (`ExportToExcel`) crashed with empty `viewname` (`getCustomViewFromFile('')` ‚Üí ‚ÄûNie znaleziono widoku‚Äù) because this related list has **no cvid dropdown** (`CUSTOM_VIEW_LIST = []`).

## ListPreview empty state (do not regress)

- `ProjektyRekrutacyjne/RelatedList.tpl` ListPreview branch: the `empty($RELATED_RECORDS)` case **must still `{include RelatedListContents.tpl}`** so column headers + per-column search survive filtering to zero (else user loses filters and can't clear them). Matches Base related-list behavior: **no ‚ÄûLista jest pusta‚Äù message** ‚Äî just an empty `tbody`. Empty wrapper uses `.c-list-preview--empty` (`float:none; width:100%`).
- Narrow checkbox/action columns: tightened in `RelatedList.css` (`.listViewEntriesTable` first two cols ‚Üí `width:1px; white-space:nowrap`) because ListPreview table is `min-width:max-content`, so `width="4%"` on `<th>` is ignored.
